		<hr size="1">Gtheb:</P><P>EQ1 is pretty much a dead game as far as the Dark Army is concerned.  They never managed to establish a true PvP server, even on Rallos Zek where I played. With no item degradation most high level peeps have huge stores of items saved in the bank. Plus they continue to create no drop quest items which undermined the PvP incentive.  Instead of making a true PvP environment, Sony game us another watered down blue server when they developed the Zek servers.  (Since 90% of EQ members play on blue servers they cater to them even on the supposed PvP servers)</P><P>So, to answer your question, EQ1 will never have a dynamic PvP environment.  It’s not set up to be that way.  Even when I had my guild sweeping down on the peeps in the Freeport area, the game system and administrators fought us every step of the way.  I’ve heard that EQ2 will make some improvements to PvP combat but I doubt they’ll do it justice. They cater too much to the care bears that play (the majority of players) and not to the wolves that trim the flock.</P><P>PK<BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
